comments.body:
Not really... The code in lines 265-269 handles the verbose output while 271-272 just removes one layer for output for volumes so getting the selected keys is simplified as per earlier recommendation. Those are two different actions. 
There is an additional key `Warnings` in `volumes` output and if we aim to return whole API reply in verbose this should be included as well, see an example from the API documentation

```
{
  "Volumes": [
    {
      "CreatedAt": "2017-07-19T12:00:26Z",
      "Name": "tardis",
      "Driver": "local",
      "Mountpoint": "/var/lib/docker/volumes/tardis",
      "Labels": {
        "com.example.some-label": "some-value",
        "com.example.some-other-label": "some-other-value"
      },
      "Scope": "local",
      "Options": {
        "device": "tmpfs",
        "o": "size=100m,uid=1000",
        "type": "tmpfs"
      }
    }
  ],
  "Warnings": []
}
```

